# Normalize ALL text files to LF in the repository and on checkout. Without this,
# `core.autocrlf=true` on Windows checkouts produces persistent CRLF-vs-LF churn —
# every text file shows as "modified" in `git status` even with no real change
# (and the working copy can break LF-sensitive tooling). See the coordination board
# 2026-06-26.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts must be LF everywhere — a CRLF working copy breaks bash
# (classic symptom: "syntax error: unexpected end of file"). Kept explicit.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Common binary assets — never normalize line endings on these.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.pdf  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
